{"TopicId":178487,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"More filters in part categories","CreatedByName":"ndiver","CreatedById":60662,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-23T14:54:24Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ndiver","CreatedById":60662,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-23T14:54:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a mod that provides more filter than \u0022Name / Mass / Cost / Size\u0022 ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTypically for the engines, that can sort the engines by Isp or by thrust?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI thank you for your answers \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Niallalva","CreatedById":189178,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-23T17:24:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure, have you tried \u0022Community Parts Tiles\u0022 it\u0027s in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E. You can also try Janitors Closet which filters by mods, also in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E(Max\u00A0KSP version 1.4.3(Though it works fine in 1.4.5 if installed manually)). I never really needed more than that to filter them. Not sure about Isp or thrust have you tried the arrow in the top left corner of the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/HKcjxgN\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://imgur.com/HKcjxgN\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2603684234\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/147463-14-end-your-parts-list-nightmare-introducing-the-janitors-closet/\u0026amp;tab=comments\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2751166\u0026amp;embedComment=2751166\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-2751166\u0022 style=\u0022height:309px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JH4C","CreatedById":188049,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-23T20:49:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EJC\u003C/strong\u003E (mentioned above) and\u003Cstrong\u003E Filter Extensions\u003C/strong\u003E offer many extra ways of filtering your parts and mods, but I don\u0027t think either offer a new column in the parts window to use for weighting. I\u0027d love one for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Specific Impulse (rocketry) or Internet Service Provider\u0022\u003EISP\u003C/abbr\u003E and/or kN/MN thrust, but in lieu I just filter by the engine type I want and then by price; the more expensive engines tend to have the higher power ratios.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2837791055\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/168456-14-filter-extensions-no-localization/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:225px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}